no.motif.types

Interface Elements<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the contained elements.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Appendable<T>, Filterable<T>, Mappable<T>, Prependable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PreparedIterable

    public interface Elements<T>
extends Mappable<T>, Filterable<T>, Appendable<T>, Prependable<T>
    This is a reactor type, gathering the collection operations which is implemented lazily by Motif. Methods that only need to append, prepend, and/or in any way adapt the elements of a collection can accept this type as method argument to ensure, as well as communicating to the callee, that no iterating will take place.
    See Also:
    PreparedIterable
